words.name: dilemmatic
definitions: in logic, pertaining to or of the nature of a dilemma.

words.name: insolubleness
definitions: the quality of being insoluble.

words.name: affreighter
definitions: one who hires or charters a ship to transport goods.

words.name: calends
definitions: the day of the new moon and the first day of the month in the ancient Roman calendar.

words.name: talon
definitions: a sharp hooked claw especially on a bird of prey.

words.name: eloign
definitions: to remove or carry away to a distance, especially so as to conceal.

words.name: vat
definitions: A large vessel, such as a tub, cistern, or barrel, used to hold or store liquids.

words.name: fascicular
definitions: related to plants or animals or crystals having aciculae or needle-like parts.

words.name: rosette
definitions: an ornament or pattern resembling a rose that is worn as a badge of office or as recognition of having won an honor.
a cluster of leaves growing in crowded circles from a common center or crown (usually at or close to the ground).
circular window filled with tracery

words.name: spatulate
definitions: of a leaf shape.
having a broad rounded apex and a narrow base.

words.name: looter
definitions: one who loots, who steals during a general disturbance such as a riot or natural disaster.

words.name: barrater
definitions: someone guilty of barratry.

words.name: periclean
definitions: of or relating to Pericles (about 495-429 b. c.), the foremost citizen and practically chief of the state of ancient Athens at her greatest period; hence, pertaining to the age of the intellectual and material preeminence of Athens.

words.name: podophyllin
definitions: a bitter-tasting resin obtained from the dried root of the May apple and used in medicine as a cathartic and caustic.

words.name: baetyl
definitions: a meteorite or similar-looking rough stone thought to be of divine origin and worshipped as sacred.

words.name: bedouin
definitions: a member of a nomadic tribe of Arabs.

words.name: uncongenial
definitions: not compatible or sympathetic, as in character.
not appropriate; unsuitable

words.name: photometry
definitions: measurement of the proterties of light (especially luminous intensity).
in biology, the reactional movement, positive and negative, with an indifference point between, of organisms under changing intensity of illumination.

words.name: vernal
definitions: of or characteristic of or occurring in spring.
suggestive of youth; vigorous and fresh

words.name: overcrop
definitions: to exhaust the fertility of (land) by continuous cultivation of crops.

words.name: septet
definitions: a musical composition written for seven performers.
seven people considered as a unit.

words.name: addressograph
definitions: a device for producing mailing labels first produced in 1893, used in much of the 20th century.

words.name: calumniation
definitions: a false accusation of an offense or a malicious misrepresentation of someone's words or actions.

words.name: convocation
definitions: a group gathered in response to a summons.

words.name: delude
definitions: be false to; be dishonest with.

words.name: freethinking
definitions: the doctrine that reason is the right basis for regulating conduct.

words.name: palliate
definitions: lessen or to try to lessen the seriousness or extent of.
provide physical relief, as from pain

words.name: uncarved
definitions: not having been carved or shaped with knife or other tool.
natural, unmodified, pristine

words.name: arcadianism
definitions: rustic or pastoral simplicity, especially as affected in literature; specifically, in Italian literature about the end of the seventeenth century, the affectation of classic simplicity.

words.name: pibgorn
definitions: an ancient (now obsolete) single-reed woodwind; usually made of bone.
